\section{Conclusions.}

\frame{
\tableofcontents[ 
    currentsubsection, 
    sectionstyle=show/hide, 
    sectionstyle=show/shaded, 
    ] 
}

\frame{
\begin{itemize}
 \item We developed a method for the automatic classification of galaxy clusters dynamical state. \pause
 \item Using this technique we build a catalogue of merging clusters candidates. \pause
 \item We performed individual analysis of $3$ of this clusters. \pause
 \item We performed an Statistical analysis comparing the magnetic fields in relaxed and unrelaxed clusters. \pause
 \item We studied the cosmic microwave background using Machine Learning techniques. \pause
 \item We studied the angular distributions of the cosmological parameters without finding anything unexpected in the standard cosmological model, with
       the possible exception of the parameter $10^{9}A_{s}e^{-2\tau}$.
\end{itemize}
}

\frame{
\begin{itemize}
 \item Machine Learning techniques are very powerful tools to study in an independent and agnostic way any data set.  \pause
 \item They can be very useful for classification and regression problems, achieving, in most of the problems, better results than the traditional methods 
       in lower computational time. \pause
 \item Taking into account the large amount of data that will be recorded by the future surveys, this technique will be essential
       for their analysis.
\end{itemize}
}

